name: Svend Press
description: Squeeze lightweight plates between the palms and press outwards, creating constant chest tension to effectively isolate and build the pectoral muscles.

name: Archer Push-Up
description: One-arm dominant push-up variation where one arm bears most of the load while the other remains extended, increasing demand on the chest and triceps for strength and stability.

name: Guillotine Press
description: Bench press variation lowering the barbell to the neck to emphasize upper pec fibers, allowing targeted chest development.

name: Plyometric Push-Up
description: Explosive push-up where the hands leave the floor, training the upper-body muscles to produce power and engage fast-twitch fibers.

name: Cable Iron Cross
description: Cable exercise focusing on inner chest fibers by crossing the cables in front of the body, maintaining constant tension for a deep contraction.

name: Around-the-World (Dumbbell)
description: Lying circular dumbbell movement that works the chest through a full range of motion, arcing weights to hit pec fibers from all angles.

name: Back Widow
description: Lying face-up, push the elbows into the ground to lift the torso, engaging traps, rhomboids, and rear delts to strengthen the upper back.

name: Meadows Row
description: One-arm landmine row done with a staggered stance, heavily engaging the lats and upper back while minimizing shoulder strain.

name: Seal Row
description: Chest-supported prone row that eliminates momentum, isolating the upper back and lats with strict form.

name: Inverted Row
description: Bodyweight rowing exercise performed hanging under a bar, engaging the mid-back and lats while also working the biceps.

name: Archer Pull-Up
description: Advanced pull-up variation where one arm does most of the pulling while the other remains extended, building lat and biceps strength.

name: Z Press
description: Seated floor press with legs extended, forcing the core to stabilize while pressing and building shoulder strength and stability.

name: Cuban Press
description: Three-part movement (upright row, external rotation, overhead press) strengthening the entire shoulder complex and rotator cuff.

name: Face Pull
description: Cable rope pull toward the face at eye level, targeting rear delts, traps, and external rotators to improve posture and stability.

name: Handstand Push-Up
description: Vertical bodyweight press against a wall building shoulder and triceps strength, balance, and core engagement.

name: Landmine Press (Half-Kneeling)
description: One-arm landmine press from a half-kneeling stance, working the front delts and triceps while engaging core and hips for stability.

name: Bottoms-Up Kettlebell Press
description: Overhead press holding a kettlebell upside-down, recruiting grip and rotator cuff muscles intensely for shoulder stability.

name: Zottman Curl
description: Curl up with palms up and lower with palms down, working both the biceps and forearm muscles for balanced development.

name: Spider Curl
description: Prone incline curl eliminating momentum, maximizing isolation on the biceps short head for strong peak contraction.

name: Drag Curl
description: Curl the barbell straight up along the torso by driving elbows back, minimizing shoulder involvement and keeping tension on the biceps.

name: Tate Press
description: Lying dumbbell extension with elbows flared out, isolating the medial head of the triceps and building pressing strength with reduced elbow strain.

name: Sphinx Push-Up
description: Bodyweight triceps extension from forearms to hands, shifting emphasis onto the triceps effectively using only body weight.

name: JM Press
description: Hybrid between close-grip bench press and skullcrusher, allowing heavier weight for triceps strength and improving bench lockout.

name: Farmer’s Walk
description: Walk while holding heavy weights at your sides, intensely challenging grip and forearms while engaging traps and core for stability.

name: Wrist Roller
description: Wind a weight up and down by flexing and extending the wrists, developing strength and endurance in the forearm muscles.

name: Sissy Squat
description: Rise onto toes and lean back with hips extended, placing load on quadriceps for isolation and maximal stimulation.

name: Jefferson Squat
description: Straddle-style barbell squat working legs in a different plane, increasing lower-body strength and core stability.

name: Cossack Squat
description: Deep lateral squat shifting weight side to side to improve hip, knee, and ankle mobility while strengthening inner thighs and quads.

name: Nordic Hamstring Curl
description: Lower body forward under control with ankles anchored, building hamstring strength and eccentric control.

name: Pistol Squat
description: One-legged full squat requiring balance, mobility, and strength, correcting imbalances and building unilateral leg power.

name: Reverse Hyperextension
description: Swing legs upward behind you while lying face down, strengthening glutes and hamstrings and decompressing the lower spine.

name: Donkey Calf Raise
description: Bent-over calf raise allowing a deep stretch and strong contraction, historically used to build bigger calf muscles.

name: Tibialis Anterior Raise
description: Lift forefoot toward the knee to strengthen the tibialis anterior, improving ankle stability and preventing shin splints.

name: Dragon Flag
description: Hold body straight and lower/up like a flag, developing tremendous core strength and defined abs.

name: Ab Wheel Rollout
description: Roll out with an ab wheel to challenge the entire core in resisting extension, building powerful stability.

name: Pallof Press
description: Press a band/cable straight out to resist rotation, building core stability and spine protection.

name: Stir the Pot
description: Plank on a stability ball while making circles with the arms, challenging the core in all directions for stability.

name: Copenhagen Plank
description: Side plank variation with top leg on a bench, intensely targeting adductors and lateral core for injury prevention.

name: Dead Bug
description: Alternate lowering opposite arm and leg from supine position, keeping lower back flat to train deep core stability.

name: Hanging Windshield Wipers
description: Hang from a bar and swing legs side to side like a wiper, demanding oblique strength and hip flexor control.
